
// This Hyperlambda code evaluates to true if either the [stream] argument is explicitly set to false or if the [stream] argument does not exist at all. It uses the [or] slot to combine these two conditions, where the first condition checks for equality with false using [eq], and the second condition checks for the non-existence of the [stream] argument using [not-exists].
or
   eq:x:@.arguments/*/stream
      .:bool:false
   not-exists:x:@.arguments/*/stream
